      {
        "question_id": "Q1",
        "topic_used": "nth term of an ap",
        "scenario_text": "Aarav is helping his grandfather organize a plantation drive in their village garden. They decide to plant saplings in a perfectly straight line, ensuring there is a fixed, equal gap between every consecutive sapling to allow enough room for the roots to spread. Aarav uses a long measuring tape starting from the very first sapling to mark the exact spots where the subsequent saplings should be placed. As the row grows longer, he notices that the distance from the starting point to each new sapling follows a steady increasing pattern.",
